    "long_instructions": "## Do This\r\n\r\n1. In your `custom.py` file create three functions called `collect_paint`, `navigate_to_new_location`, and `paint_a_path`.\r\n2. `collect_paint` should use a `while painter.is_on_bucket` loop to collect all the paint from a bucket.\r\n3. `navigate_to_new_location` should use a `while painter.can_move` loop to move to a new location in The Neighborhood.\r\n4. `paint_a_path` should use the `paint()` and `move()` methods to paint a path of a set length.\r\n5. Use all three functions together to navigate and paint throughout The Neighborhood.\r\n    - Hint: Remember to use the `turn_left()` and `turn_right()` functions as needed.\r\n\r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n",
